# CLH October 2025 Newsletter

Hi CLH family,

Hope this finds you all well\!

Our team at Creative Learning Haven wants to share some exciting updates\!

1\. **You can now order CLH postcards** to be delivered to you (suggested $5/postcard), featuring art created by Lemi Samuel and Meta Richard, two of our CLH artists\! Each envelope will come with a special message from a youth artist\! We've already sold out of our first round, and we're currently re-printing for a second round of postcards :) 

**ORDER HERE:** [https://forms.gle/jGzUC9CV1rBaSKbj9](https://forms.gle/jGzUC9CV1rBaSKbj9) 

![Postcard\_googleforms.png][image1]

2\. We showed artwork from the libraries at the reception of a **documentary screening at MIT on October 3\!** The screening was for [Design for Our Lives](https://youtu.be/Q28wQbm7_Hs), a 55 minute documentary directed by CLH co-founder Lulu Tian. The film follows 4 stories of East African innovators changing their communities through design, engineering, and education. 

![welcome center CLH collage.png][image2]  
*Photos taken by CLH volunteer Bennett Y. Featuring volunteers: Isabella H., Claire Y.*

This film led to the start of Creative Learning Haven, because it's how Lulu first traveled to Imvepi and Rhino refugee camps and met Hope Rising South Sudan \+ YSAT, our two local partners. This screening was very full circle\!

* **If you or anybody you know would be interested in watching this film, please email luluyaotian@gmail.com\!**   
* The film sparks conversation about the role of design \+ engineering in different East African contexts, and what collaboration between American universities and East African organizations & community members could look like. 

![Design for Our Lives.png][image3]

3\. CLH is holding **an event this Sunday 2PM** at Griffin Museum of Photography in Winchester, MA\! 

* RSVP Here: [https://www.eventbrite.com/e/art-activities-libraries-in-ugandas-refugee-camps-tickets-1902194728639?aff=oddtdtcreator](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/art-activities-libraries-in-ugandas-refugee-camps-tickets-1902194728639?aff=oddtdtcreator)  
* **Join us to learn about libraries in Uganda's refugee camps, see art and photography by refugee youths, and create art of your own\!** Open to all ages, and great for kids, youths, and families\!

![IMG\_3431 (1).png][image4]

**4\. Continued Impact in Imvepi and Rhino**

* **We've now reached over 1,000 unique individuals in Imvepi and Rhino\!**   
* Our Media Team is active in creating update videos \+ interviewing library visitors\!   
  * Interview with Emma, a community leader: [https://www.instagram.com/p/DQmSdiAjRIl/](https://www.instagram.com/p/DQmSdiAjRIl/)  
  * Interview with Emilly, a library visitor: [https://www.instagram.com/p/DQEX8ZoDZdE/](https://www.instagram.com/p/DQEX8ZoDZdE/)  
* **Activity spotlight: Women's Group\!** We've started conducting literacy classes for the 20 mothers and out-of-school women who have been with us since March, learning to knit and craft marketable products. Look at the lovely bags they made last month\!\!
